WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:12.480
Oxford bookworms, starters, the 15th character by Rosemary Bauder, read by Nick Mercer, published

00:12.480 --> 00:19.480
and copyright, Oxford University Press 2000.

00:19.480 --> 00:29.560
Chapter 1 Jobs for Today

00:29.560 --> 00:36.640
Every day, lots of different people come to Happy Hills, because there are lots of exciting

00:36.640 --> 00:40.440
things to do.

00:40.440 --> 00:45.520
Sally Brown works at Happy Hills in her holiday.

00:45.520 --> 00:50.440
She is a student, and she wants to be a teacher.

00:50.440 --> 01:00.080
I need the money, she tells her family, and it's an interesting job.

01:00.080 --> 01:06.840
But she is always very tired in the evening.

01:06.840 --> 01:12.640
The workers at Happy Hills arrive early in the morning.

01:12.640 --> 01:18.920
They all wear clean green trousers and yellow shirts.

01:18.920 --> 01:26.200
They must smile a lot and be nice to all the visitors.

01:26.200 --> 01:35.760
Every morning, Mr. Parry puts a list of jobs for today in the workers' canteen.

01:35.760 --> 01:40.360
Mr. Parry wears different clothes.

01:40.360 --> 01:52.920
His shirt is green, and his trousers are white, and he wears a red coat with I'm Ken Parry.

01:52.920 --> 01:54.960
Can I help you?

01:54.960 --> 01:57.800
On his pocket.

01:57.800 --> 02:06.960
The visitors call him Ken, but all the workers call him Mr. Parry.

02:06.960 --> 02:14.800
Today, Sally arrives at Happy Hills at eight o'clock.

02:14.800 --> 02:23.960
On her shirt, there is a picture of a smiling face, and have a happy day in black and red

02:23.960 --> 02:26.840
writing.

02:26.840 --> 02:35.000
She goes to the canteen and looks for Mr. Parry's list.

02:35.000 --> 02:38.480
What job am I doing today?

02:38.480 --> 02:47.600
Sally thinks, am I making tea or helping in the children's playhouse?

02:47.600 --> 02:50.880
But Sally is wrong.

02:50.880 --> 03:01.400
The list says, Sally Brown, Connie Cat, Brake, eleven o'clock.

03:01.400 --> 03:10.200
Oh no, thinks Sally.

03:10.200 --> 03:19.760
Nobody likes wearing the costumes, but at Happy Hills, the characters are very important.

03:19.760 --> 03:28.600
The visitors like to take photos of their children with cowboy Joe, Charlie Clown, Baby

03:28.600 --> 03:42.280
Blue Eyes, Photo Fill, Big John, Connie Cat, Big Apple, Miss Flower, Edward Elephant,

03:42.280 --> 03:46.680
and all their friends.

03:46.680 --> 03:56.040
Sally always asks the same questions, are you very hot in your costume?

03:56.040 --> 04:01.720
And how do you eat and drink?

04:01.720 --> 04:05.320
Edward Elephant has the best job.

04:05.320 --> 04:09.880
He has a bag of water under his costume.

04:09.880 --> 04:14.320
He can spray the visitors with water.

04:14.320 --> 04:21.760
And Photo Fill and Charlie Clown make everybody laugh.

04:21.760 --> 04:25.960
But Connie Cat cannot do that.

04:25.960 --> 04:30.520
She can only say, meow.

04:30.520 --> 04:34.880
To the children all day.

04:34.880 --> 04:38.520
Sally looks for her costume.

04:38.520 --> 04:44.760
A tall man in a cowboy costume is standing beside her.

04:44.760 --> 04:47.800
Hello, Sally.

04:47.800 --> 04:48.960
Says the cowboy.

04:48.960 --> 04:53.640
It's me, William.

04:53.640 --> 04:56.520
William is a student too.

04:56.520 --> 04:59.920
He is Sally's friend.

04:59.920 --> 05:04.280
Which costume are you looking for?

05:04.280 --> 05:06.680
Connie Cat.

05:06.680 --> 05:09.480
When's your break?

05:09.480 --> 05:12.000
11 o'clock.

05:12.000 --> 05:18.040
Me too.

05:18.040 --> 05:20.600
Chapter Two.

05:20.600 --> 05:28.040
Here comes Zapp.

05:28.040 --> 05:30.200
It is 9 o'clock.

05:30.200 --> 05:32.280
The doors open.

05:32.280 --> 05:36.200
But there are not many visitors today.

05:36.200 --> 05:39.040
They all have invitations.

05:39.040 --> 05:42.760
And they show them to Mr. Parry.

05:42.760 --> 05:47.160
A very famous man is coming to Happy Hills.

05:47.160 --> 05:51.160
So Mr. Parry is very excited.

05:51.160 --> 05:54.160
Zapp's coming today.

05:54.160 --> 05:57.760
He's opening the new Zappocopter.

05:57.760 --> 06:01.320
Says William to Sally.

06:01.320 --> 06:05.440
Stop talking and do some work.

06:05.440 --> 06:08.960
Says Mr. Parry.

06:08.960 --> 06:11.600
Zapp is a singer.

06:11.600 --> 06:15.000
Sally loves listening to his songs.

06:15.000 --> 06:18.760
And she has all his CDs.

06:18.760 --> 06:24.160
There is a picture of him in her room too.

06:24.160 --> 06:28.920
The Zappocopter is very exciting.

06:28.920 --> 06:36.360
Zappoc can sit in little helicopters and go up and down very fast.

06:36.360 --> 06:42.640
The visitors stand behind a blue rope and wait for Zapp.

06:42.640 --> 06:47.440
Please stay behind the rope.

06:47.440 --> 06:50.520
Says Mr. Parry.

06:50.520 --> 06:55.040
Suddenly there is a noise in the sky.

06:55.040 --> 06:57.360
Everybody looks up.

06:57.360 --> 07:03.480
Zapp's helicopter says William.

07:03.480 --> 07:09.200
The helicopter comes down and Zapp gets out.

07:09.200 --> 07:12.240
He smiles at the visitors.

07:12.240 --> 07:17.160
Oh, he's wonderful.

07:17.160 --> 07:19.640
Says a young girl.

07:19.640 --> 07:23.120
She gives Zapp a flower.

07:23.120 --> 07:30.560
He gives her a big smile and says, thank you.

07:30.560 --> 07:35.200
Sally is hot and thirsty in her costume.

07:35.200 --> 07:44.880
She wants to talk too, but Mr. Parry is watching.

07:44.880 --> 07:55.040
Number three, Zapp's new song.

07:55.040 --> 07:59.400
Mr. Parry takes the singer to the Zappocopter.

07:59.400 --> 08:03.960
Zapp cuts the rope.

08:03.960 --> 08:05.720
Thank you, Zapp.

08:05.720 --> 08:10.160
Now please, can you sing for us?

08:10.160 --> 08:12.200
Says Mr. Parry.

08:12.280 --> 08:16.520
OK, but the people must help me.

08:16.520 --> 08:21.120
He says, he begins to sing.

08:21.120 --> 08:26.840
Everybody knows the song and sings it with him.

08:26.840 --> 08:30.400
Thank you, says Zapp.

08:30.400 --> 08:33.760
You're all wonderful singers.

08:33.760 --> 08:37.360
Now look at this.

08:37.360 --> 08:40.800
He takes a CD out of his pocket.

08:40.800 --> 08:44.680
This is my new song.

08:44.680 --> 08:49.680
He says, please sing it for us.

08:49.680 --> 08:52.080
Say the TV, men.

08:52.080 --> 08:54.960
But Zapp smiles.

08:54.960 --> 08:57.280
No, no.

08:57.280 --> 09:03.160
You must come to my big concert next Saturday.

09:03.160 --> 09:08.000
He puts the CD in his pocket again.

09:08.080 --> 09:14.960
Now let's go on the Zappocopter, says Zapp.

09:14.960 --> 09:19.440
He sees a teacher with some children.

09:19.440 --> 09:22.320
Would they like to come too?

09:22.320 --> 09:24.520
He asks her.

09:24.520 --> 09:28.840
Of course, says the teacher.

09:28.840 --> 09:33.600
They help the children into the helicopters.

09:33.600 --> 09:37.560
Zapp smiles and smiles.

09:37.560 --> 09:42.480
The photographers take lots of pictures.

09:42.480 --> 09:46.120
Photo fill arrives too.

09:46.120 --> 09:50.240
He is one of the Happy Hills characters.

09:50.240 --> 09:56.240
He takes a photo of the children and sprays them with water.

09:56.240 --> 09:59.960
Everybody laughs.

09:59.960 --> 10:04.080
Zapp is having a wonderful day.

10:04.160 --> 10:07.680
He speaks to the TV people.

10:07.680 --> 10:13.400
The photographers take photos of him with all the characters.

10:13.400 --> 10:16.720
Zapp meets Charlie Clown.

10:16.720 --> 10:19.320
Charlie gives him a flower.

10:19.320 --> 10:23.080
And the flower sprays him with water.

10:23.080 --> 10:26.800
Everybody laughs.

10:26.800 --> 10:29.680
Sally meets Zapp too.

10:29.680 --> 10:32.680
And she is very excited.

10:32.680 --> 10:35.400
But she cannot talk to him because she

10:35.400 --> 10:38.360
is wearing her cat costume.

10:38.360 --> 10:41.160
And Mr. Parry is watching.

10:46.040 --> 10:48.800
Chapter four.

10:48.800 --> 10:50.680
Where's Zapp's CD?

10:56.840 --> 10:57.840
Come on.

10:57.840 --> 11:01.880
It's 11 o'clock, says William.

11:01.880 --> 11:04.960
Let's go to the canteen for our break.

11:04.960 --> 11:08.840
We've got 10 minutes.

11:08.840 --> 11:14.240
They sit down in the canteen and take off their heads.

11:14.240 --> 11:16.640
Sally is thirsty.

11:16.640 --> 11:20.320
Her face is hot and red.

11:20.320 --> 11:24.480
William is hot and thirsty too.

11:24.480 --> 11:28.880
They have a long drink of cold water.

11:28.880 --> 11:33.800
That's good, William says.

11:33.800 --> 11:37.280
Then he looks at his watch.

11:37.280 --> 11:41.400
10 past 11, he says.

11:41.400 --> 11:43.120
Come on, Sally.

11:43.120 --> 11:43.760
Back to work.

11:46.680 --> 11:52.320
They finish their drinks and put their heads on again.

11:52.320 --> 11:57.400
Suddenly, a lot of people come into the canteen.

11:57.400 --> 12:01.800
Watch the matter, says William.

12:01.800 --> 12:06.680
Zapp's CD, says Mr. Parry.

12:06.680 --> 12:10.320
He can't find it.

12:10.320 --> 12:13.520
Everybody is unhappy.

12:13.520 --> 12:17.840
But Zapp is angry too.

12:17.840 --> 12:21.880
That's CD's important, Parry.

12:21.880 --> 12:26.440
He says, you must find it.

12:26.440 --> 12:29.960
I'm doing my best, Zapp.

12:29.960 --> 12:31.720
Says Mr. Parry.

12:31.720 --> 12:34.040
Don't hit me, please.

12:34.040 --> 12:35.680
I'm doing my best.

12:38.960 --> 12:43.120
A lot of things happen very quickly.

12:43.120 --> 12:46.400
The visitors want to go home.

12:46.400 --> 12:51.840
But suddenly, Mr. Parry closes all the doors.

12:51.840 --> 12:54.560
Nobody can leave.

12:54.560 --> 12:56.040
He says.

12:56.040 --> 13:01.400
I'm sorry, but Zapp's CD is very important,

13:01.400 --> 13:05.400
and we must find it.

13:05.400 --> 13:09.840
Mr. Parry makes a telephone call.

13:09.840 --> 13:16.280
Very soon, four police arrive in a big white police car.

13:16.280 --> 13:17.680
They ask a lot of questions.

13:20.680 --> 13:24.720
The police look everywhere for the CD.

13:24.720 --> 13:28.880
They read Mr. Parry's list of visitors.

13:28.880 --> 13:31.760
They count the visitors carefully

13:31.760 --> 13:36.760
and look in all their pockets and bags.

13:36.760 --> 13:39.520
There is a lot of noise.

13:39.520 --> 13:43.160
People are angry and tired.

13:43.160 --> 13:46.440
They want to go home now.

13:46.440 --> 13:54.360
And Zapp is speaking very quietly into a little black telephone.

13:54.360 --> 14:01.000
Photo fill goes to him and says, smile, please.

14:01.000 --> 14:07.640
Go away, says Zapp angrily.

14:07.640 --> 14:11.840
Now the police want to talk to the workers.

14:11.840 --> 14:15.800
One stays with the visitors, and three police

14:15.800 --> 14:19.720
speak to the workers in the canteen.

14:19.720 --> 14:23.360
Zapp comes with the police.

14:23.360 --> 14:29.200
You must find that CD, says Zapp.

14:29.200 --> 14:32.000
We're doing our best, Zapp.

14:32.000 --> 14:32.920
Say the police.

14:38.360 --> 14:42.640
Chapter 5, the 15th character.

14:48.800 --> 14:51.840
Sally waits quietly with the other workers.

14:53.920 --> 15:02.000
She looks at Mr. Parry's jobs for today list and counts the names.

15:02.000 --> 15:06.560
There are 29 names on the list today.

15:06.560 --> 15:10.400
15 people are helpers.

15:10.400 --> 15:17.520
They wear green trousers and yellow shirts and help the visitors.

15:17.600 --> 15:26.080
14 people are characters and wear costumes.

15:26.080 --> 15:28.400
Wait a minute.

15:28.400 --> 15:30.520
Think Sally.

15:30.520 --> 15:34.240
There are 14 characters on the list,

15:34.240 --> 15:39.080
but there are 15 characters here.

15:39.080 --> 15:45.360
She reads the list again very, very carefully.

15:45.360 --> 15:47.600
Edward Elephant.

15:47.600 --> 15:50.480
Yes, he's here.

15:50.480 --> 15:52.680
Connie Cat.

15:52.680 --> 15:54.680
That's me.

15:54.680 --> 15:57.320
Cowboy Joe.

15:57.320 --> 15:59.280
That's William.

15:59.280 --> 16:01.720
Photo fill.

16:01.720 --> 16:04.240
Yes, he's here.

16:04.240 --> 16:06.280
Big Apple.

16:06.280 --> 16:08.360
Yes.

16:08.360 --> 16:14.520
So laugh a lot and lady love a little.

16:14.520 --> 16:16.600
Wait a minute.

16:16.600 --> 16:19.880
Charlie Clown isn't on the list,

16:19.880 --> 16:24.920
but Charlie's here in this room.

16:24.920 --> 16:29.680
Excuse me, Mr. Parry, says Sally.

16:29.680 --> 16:33.400
There are 14 characters on your list,

16:33.400 --> 16:37.200
but there are 15 in the room now.

16:37.200 --> 16:43.200
Charlie Clown isn't on the list, but he's here.

16:43.200 --> 16:48.320
Mr. Parry reads the list and counts the characters.

16:48.320 --> 16:54.920
You're right, Sally, he says.

16:54.920 --> 17:01.440
Take off your heads, Mr. Parry says to the characters.

17:01.440 --> 17:04.960
They take off their heads.

17:04.960 --> 17:09.680
Charlie Clown is a woman.

17:09.680 --> 17:13.600
Why are you wearing that costume?

17:13.600 --> 17:16.480
Asks Mr. Parry.

17:16.480 --> 17:23.520
The woman begins to run away, but William stops her.

17:23.520 --> 17:30.200
The police take off her costume and find a big pocket.

17:30.200 --> 17:34.080
In it they find Sap's CD.

17:34.080 --> 17:39.320
The singer smiles again.

17:39.320 --> 17:41.920
It is Saturday night.

17:41.920 --> 17:49.200
Sally and William are in London because they're going to Zap's concert.

17:49.200 --> 17:57.160
There are lots of excited people and TV photographers outside the hall.

17:57.160 --> 18:00.600
Everybody wants to hear Zap's new song.

18:01.600 --> 18:04.600
Where are your tickets?

18:04.600 --> 18:08.600
Says the man at the door to Sally.

18:08.600 --> 18:13.600
We haven't got any tickets, says Sally.

18:13.600 --> 18:18.600
The man begins to look angry.

18:18.600 --> 18:24.600
Sally smiles and takes something out of her pocket.

18:24.600 --> 18:27.600
Is this invitation okay?

18:27.600 --> 18:31.600
It's from Zap.

